The newly inaugurated Governor of Anambra State, Prof Chukwuma Soludo, has promised citizens of the state that his government would make them proud. DAILY POST had earlier reported that the former Governor of Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) was sworn-in by the state Chief Judge, Justice Onochie Anyachebelu at exactly 9:45 am at the Anambra State Government House on Thursday. In his speech, the governor who lauded his supporters across the country assured that he is assuming the office to serve the people of the state. The governor recalled the incident that occurred in his village in 2021 where about three police officers were killed by unknown gunmen. He pledged that his administration would continue to take care of the families of the slain police officers. He said, “This is the moment. I applied for this job, with my party, APGA and you citizens of the state permitted me to be your servant. God ordained this moment and we are grateful to him and to you all for the privilege to serve you. “I and my deputy will work hard every day to make you proud. I remember three police officers who lost their lives to unknown gunmen that attacked us in a meeting with the youths in my village last year. We pledge to continue to take care of their families”.